About
*****


 @{" Disclaimers                       " link "Disclaimers"}  - Legal mush
 @{" Registration                      " link "Registration"}  - How to register
 @{" Features                          " link "Features"}  - Features
 @{" Thanks                            " link "Thanks"}  - A big list of thanks
 @{" Quotes                            " link "Quotes"}  - What the magazines say about Thor

THOR is developed for saving online time on Bulletin Board Systems and
the Internet, by allowing the user to build a database of messages that
can be manipulated offline.  And, of course, for the simple pleasure of
creating the best offline reader on the Amiga

The team behind THOR is

Petter Nilsen,  Eivind  Nordseth,  Kjell  Irgens,  Magne Řstlyngen,
Troels Walsted Hansen and Borge Nost.

Petter  is  the team coordinator and creator of the THOR main program,
including  look  and  feel.  He has also made ConfigTHOR, ConnectTHOR,
and various other programs. He is also the maintainer of utgui.library
and bbsread.library starting from 2.4 of THOR.

Eivind  is responsible for the database functionality in THOR.  He has
also  written the NComm scripts, the ABBS module, and part of the UUCP
module.

Kjell  has  made  the  UUCP,  QWK,  SOUP,  TCP  (GetTCP  and SendTCP),
BlueWave, Hippo and Omen modules for THOR.  He has also done the major
part of THOR's mime compliance.

Magne  has  done  much  of  the work in making THOR font sensitive and
rescalable.   He  has  made  the  utgui-library, which contains THOR's
layout-engine  and custom gadgets.  He has also made the Fido modules,
and done a considerable amount of work on the utnet.library.

Marius Mortensen created the internal editor which have lately been
maintained by Borge Nost.

If you want to reach us with comments and/or bug reports, contact us in
either of the following ways:

@{i}     Internet: @{ui}
     
       EMail: @{b}thor@thule.no@{ub} (THOR Development Team)
         WWW: @{b}http://www.thule.no/thor/@{ub}
        News: @{b}alt.sys.amiga.thor@{ub}
     
     @{i}Snail-Mail: @{ui}
     
       Ultima Thule Software
       Attn. Petter Nilsen
       Delebekken 2
       N-1295 OSLO
       NORWAY


@endnode

